(90, 18, '#', NULL, '<p><strong>Is astrology antithetical to Karma?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Many people argue that astrology basic tenet is destiny is fixed and we can&rsquo;t change it which means it is in opposition to karma.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Let me clarify that astrology is not the opposite of karma. It is totally aligned with Karma. It is to guide your karma. Astrology is not about what will happen but what conditions or obstacles you are likely to face and what karmic path you should take in the order of handling your obstacle.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It is like a roadmap. The path through which you will travel will remain the same but it will guide you where you have to put a brake and where accelerator so that your journey is smooth.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It is like when you have a navigator, you become relax and make your action tuned accordingly.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Let me give you an example. One of my client&nbsp;was facing some marital issue. When I checked both the chart, the only problem was some key behavioural area of both sides. After chart analysis, she was able to understand more of the spouse expectation and natural tendencies. I told her what behavioural changes she should make in herself to handle it. She put in those efforts and now their married life has become smoother. I will not say there are no issues but it has become better than in the past.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Treat astrology not as medium to just know your future but a karmic roadmap that can guide you on what actions you should take which will reduce your karmic debts and make life smoother and peaceful.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Remember, Astrology is a tool to guide your karma and making you a better person by knowing yourself and your karmic patterns.</p>', '1', '2021-02-24 08:08:53.112290', '2021-02-24 12:56:36.924065'),
